<br>
But at that point we started to lose to many well geared folks to guilds that could promise them Time and it was obvious that we could never get their with our small raid size.  It was very discouraging.  We had a solid core of close friends and usually raided with 20-30 or so.  We had no desire to zerg up to 70 (or even 50 - sorry 50 is not a small family guild).  <br>
<br>
EQ needs raiding content aimed at small guilds that allows you to progress through the game.  LDoN helped a little but SoE really missed the boat on the LDoN raids - they should have been for the small guilds that were not elemental flagged.  Elemental and Time guilds hated LDoN raids - those raids could have been a life savior for small family guilds.<br>
<br>
Mitzey<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aabidano>Aabidano</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#330000>(6/1/04 9:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19439.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sigh</span><hr size=1> Just to throw in my 2 cents, the problem started at SoV, which was primarily aimed at raiding.<br>
<br>
Kunark and the old world were aimed at single groups for the most part, and it took a lot more content to keep the same number of people occupied.  (Remember when Chardok, Seb and HS were scary?)  They realized at that point (SoV) they could tie more people up longer, on less content reducing development expenses.  SoL was a little worse, with timesinks to get very far, though both it and SoV did have some decent &quot;level 60 non-hardcore player&quot; content.<br>
<br>
Then comes PoP, unless you were willing to devote large quantities of time, you weren't going anywhere.  The game was pretty much over.  They fixed that somewhat when they opened up the lower tier zones, throwing a bone to the non-raiders that were leaving in droves.<br>
<br>
LoY always has people in it, leveling, farming etc.., regardless of what people say.  Hates Fury is probably only unused zone.<br>
<br>
LDoN was neat, but limited and got boring quickly.  I'd guess it was fast and cheap to develop.<br>
<br>
GoD again focused on the top 10-15%, who don't really pay the bills at SoE.  It's very easy to get levels\AAs, but the gear to survive\progress essentially requires you to be in a raiding guild.  Something that 80% don't have time to do.  If you were to cheapen it (like PoP) people will just burn through it (in their bazaar gear) and be bored again.<br>
<br>
How to fix it without pissing even more people off?  Damned if I know.<br>
<br>
Allowing the easy, primarily outdoor leveling pipeline that emerged three(?) years ago to continue was the begining of the end I guess. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kirico>Kirico</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#330000>(6/1/04 9:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19439.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sigh</span><hr size=1> Interesting.  On Prexus the top guilds did their best to block each other (and everyone else) from progressing.  This allowed them to keep and farm the high end stuff to their heart's content.<br>
<br>
This even trickled down to the second wave of guilds getting into the elementals- they in turn did their best to block the third wave.<br>
<br>
Now everyone is pretty amendable.  There are pickup raids that people can go to and people generally play nice (in PoP).  I have no idea how it goes in GoD.<br>
<br>
These observations are from talking to friends in 'uber' guilds and one time I was invited to a RZ raid that was happening specifically to block a rival guild from doing it.<br>
