<br>
When I mean rotations I mean take a mob like king tormax.  If no one can kill him, anyone can try.<br>
<br>
Once someone kills king tormax they have a rotation with themselves. At anytime another guild that has not killed king tormax wants to try it, they have free run at him any time they wish.<br>
<br>
Once two or more guilds are on the kill list, they take turns with day long windows on spawn. Tormax spawns, guild up for him has 24 hours to kill, hoildays like thanksgiving effectively ignored in that time period(normally window goes to 48 hours).<br>
<br>
So what's the end result to all of this? Anyone that wants to kill King tormax needs to be up on rotation for it or have never killed him. Meaning if someone is from a ele+ guild, they are not killing tormax because their guild autopasses and voids their attempt.<br>
<br>
The one exception to all this is that if it is a patch night, any major mobs still up go free for all so the odd 5 man group can come and hit KT... IF he's up. King tormax is normally not available for freeforall.<br>
<br>
The same would apply to a pick up raids (they would become a 'guild' in function) I guess but my sever was so gutted on the server split, there's simply not enough unguilded people to support pick up raids.<br>
<br>
So basicly for the last 3 years, there has been no jumping in line (well the guilds that tried it earned mass enimies who would trample all over their rotation days) and all mobs from gore on up are on rotation so long as some guild expresses interest. The first real mob that was abandoned by guilds was trakanon I think as I've seen him up more than a few times and helped take him down for a possible undead bard pop.  IT did take years for that guy to be abondoned btw.<br>
<br>
So really, it's so structured on my server, someone people are driven mad lol.<br>
<br>
Cheers!<br>
